    SideOutputExample

    public static final class SideOutputExample.Tokenizer
extends ProcessFunction<java.lang.String,Tuple2<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer>>
    Implements the string tokenizer that splits sentences into words as a user-defined FlatMapFunction. The function takes a line (String) and splits it into multiple pairs in the form of "(word,1)" (Tuple2<String, Integer>).

    This rejects words that are longer than 5 characters long.

      • processElement

        public void processElement(java.lang.String value,
                           ProcessFunction.Context ctx,
                           Collector<Tuple2<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer>> out)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        从类复制的说明: ProcessFunction
        Process one element from the input stream.

        This function can output zero or more elements using the Collector parameter and also update internal state or set timers using the ProcessFunction.Context parameter.

        指定者:
        processElement 在类中 ProcessFunction<java.lang.String,Tuple2<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer>>
        参数:
        value - The input value.
        ctx - A ProcessFunction.Context that allows querying the timestamp of the element and getting a TimerService for registering timers and querying the time. The context is only valid during the invocation of this method, do not store it.
        out - The collector for returning result values.
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - This method may throw exceptions. Throwing an exception will cause the operation to fail and may trigger recovery.
